            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="742" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d742">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/10–945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Tim Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gallman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-09">October 9,
                            1945</date>.<lb/>[Received October 9—7:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10527. Press gives wide coverage to news stories from Palestine concerning
                    apprehension there of impending disorders, cessation of leave for British
                    forces, and mass meetings of Jews urging abolition of White Paper restrictions
                    on immigration. Locally it is reported that Foreign Secretary Bevin spent
                    several hours yesterday discussing Palestine situation with Mr. George Hall,
                    Colonial Secretary, and Azzam Bey, Secretary General of Arab League. It is added
                    that he also saw Dr. Weizmann, head of Jewish Agency for Palestine, during
                    weekend.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gallman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
